WEBVTT

00:01.227 --> 00:04.819
♪<i> It seems today</i>
<i> that all you see</i> ♪

00:04.839 --> 00:08.065
♪<i> Is violence in movies</i>
<i> and sex on TV</i> ♪

00:08.234 --> 00:11.677
♪<i> But where are those</i>
<i> good old-fashioned values</i> ♪

00:11.828 --> 00:14.680
♪<i> On which we used to rely?</i> ♪

00:14.831 --> 00:18.242
♪<i> Lucky there's a family guy</i> ♪

00:18.260 --> 00:21.336
♪<i> Lucky there's a man who</i>
<i> positively can do</i> ♪

00:21.430 --> 00:23.022
♪<i> All the things that make us</i> ♪

00:23.173 --> 00:24.339
♪<i> Laugh and cry</i> ♪

00:24.433 --> 00:30.237
♪<i> He's... a...</i>
<i> Fam... ily... Guy!</i> ♪

00:35.444 --> 00:38.186
<i> Good evening. Coming up,</i>
<i> a major Hollywood movie</i>

00:38.280 --> 00:39.930
<i> is set to film in Quahog.</i>

00:39.948 --> 00:41.540
<i> But first,</i>
<i> whoever recorded me</i>

00:41.691 --> 00:43.600
<i> cursing at</i>
<i> that freeway off-ramp veteran,</i>

00:43.602 --> 00:45.711
<i> please don't post that,</i>
<i> all right, seriously.</i>

00:45.862 --> 00:47.454
<i> We all have bad days.</i>

00:47.531 --> 00:49.956
<i> Our top story:</i>
<i> the latest Brad Pitt film</i>

00:50.051 --> 00:51.383
<i> will be shot</i>
<i> right here in Quahog.</i>

00:51.535 --> 00:53.777
<i> Pitt will play</i>
<i> former New Jersey governor</i>

00:53.870 --> 00:54.720
<i> Chris Christie.</i>

00:54.947 --> 00:57.114
Brad Pitt is playing
Chris Christie?!

00:57.207 --> 00:59.207
It should be a fat guy
playing that role!

00:59.226 --> 01:02.619
Chris Christie didn't eat
10,000 Jersey Mike's subs

01:02.638 --> 01:04.712
just to be played
by a Hollywood pretty boy.

01:04.732 --> 01:07.808
That's offensive, and I,
for one, will not stand for it.

01:07.960 --> 01:10.794
Although that's mostly
due to cardiovascular disease.

01:10.813 --> 01:12.071
I got to sit down.

01:12.222 --> 01:14.239
Peter, you know, you've
actually got a valid point.

01:14.391 --> 01:16.224
Oh, boy. Here comes the soapbox.

01:16.393 --> 01:18.969
It's shameful Hollywood would
pass over the many talented

01:19.062 --> 01:21.747
plus-sized actors who are
much more deserving of the role.

01:21.898 --> 01:23.323
-Name two.
-Jonah Hill?

01:23.475 --> 01:24.991
-He's thin now.
-Uh, Fat Albert?

01:25.160 --> 01:26.568
-Not real.
-James Corden?

01:26.645 --> 01:28.236
He's been canceled
for sending eggs back.

01:28.330 --> 01:30.831
Well, it's just another example
of Hollywood's history

01:30.983 --> 01:32.482
of exclusionary casting,

01:32.501 --> 01:35.410
-whitewashing and thin-washing.
-Exactly.

01:35.429 --> 01:37.988
Like Mike Myers playing
an Indian man in<i> The Love Guru.</i>

01:38.081 --> 01:40.173
-[giggles]
-Or Marlon and Shawn Wayans

01:40.250 --> 01:42.326
-playing<i> White Chicks.</i>
-[giggles]

01:42.344 --> 01:44.419
Or Mickey Rooney playing
an offensive stereotype

01:44.438 --> 01:46.496
of an Asian man
in<i> Breakfast at Tiffany's.</i>

01:46.590 --> 01:48.682
I don't know that movie,
but I like breakfast.

01:48.776 --> 01:50.334
Oh, come on, you two.

01:50.352 --> 01:52.502
You're really offended that
one of the biggest movie stars

01:52.521 --> 01:56.022
on the planet is coming to
our crap town to shoot a movie?

01:56.175 --> 01:57.858
I mean, Brad Pitt could put it
anywhere,

01:58.010 --> 01:59.843
-with any of us.
-Facts.

01:59.845 --> 02:02.788
I mean, when was the last time
a celebrity visited Quahog?

02:02.981 --> 02:04.848
-Uh, Jared Fogle.
-Who?

02:04.867 --> 02:06.032
The Subway Guy. Remember?

02:06.127 --> 02:07.534
He was here
for a public appearance.

02:07.611 --> 02:08.869
Took a shine to Chris
for some reason.

02:09.021 --> 02:10.129
Took him camping.

02:10.280 --> 02:12.113
Had these weird candies
he'd only let Chris eat.

02:12.133 --> 02:14.374
How come I don't remember
any of this?

02:14.526 --> 02:16.209
Ah, too many video games,
buddy.

02:16.362 --> 02:17.785
They're rotting your brains.

02:17.805 --> 02:20.046
Get your hands off me, Jared!

02:20.199 --> 02:22.123
You're really gonna complain
about Brad Pitt?

02:22.143 --> 02:24.217
Who cares what role
he's playing?!

02:24.370 --> 02:25.627
Well, that's easy
for you to say, Lois.

02:25.646 --> 02:28.480
Women have no idea
what it's like for us men,

02:28.632 --> 02:30.465
being held up to
impossible standards of beauty

02:30.484 --> 02:31.600
in the media.

02:31.710 --> 02:33.877
Ooh, Jennifer Lawrence has
a new movie.

02:33.896 --> 02:35.379
Eh! Too old. Next.

02:35.397 --> 02:37.047
Peter, I think
you're right to protest.

02:37.065 --> 02:38.715
-I'll even join you.
-Thanks, Brian.

02:38.734 --> 02:41.476
Sometimes you just got
to stand up for what's right.

02:41.495 --> 02:43.495
That's why I stood up
to Kanye West.

02:43.647 --> 02:46.406
Dinosaurs were created
by the Illuminati.

02:46.558 --> 02:49.168
The government hides secrets
in SpaghettiOs.

02:49.319 --> 02:50.818
And Hitler would've
won Wimbledon

02:50.913 --> 02:52.579
if he played tennis, bro.

02:52.731 --> 02:54.414
Sir, sir, sir.

02:54.566 --> 02:57.176
We do not wear shoes
in this house.

02:58.570 --> 03:02.055
Thank you. Now please
continue about Wimbledon.

03:04.243 --> 03:06.018
[chanting]
Overweight is overdue!

03:06.169 --> 03:07.186
Overweight is overdue!

03:07.337 --> 03:09.188
Wow, I'm impressed, Peter.

03:09.339 --> 03:10.856
Yeah, it's going great.

03:11.007 --> 03:12.691
News trucks even showed up
to cover it.

03:12.842 --> 03:15.343
I-I think... I think those
are just food trucks.

03:15.437 --> 03:18.088
Come on, you know you want some.

03:18.106 --> 03:19.347
Hi, fellas.

03:19.366 --> 03:21.591
Oh, hey. Thanks for coming out
to support us.

03:21.685 --> 03:24.077
"Dangerous Curves Ahead."

03:25.372 --> 03:27.931
-Oh...
-[laughs] Right?

03:27.950 --> 03:30.042
[laughs]
Oh, that is good.

03:30.193 --> 03:31.935
[laughing]
You get it.

03:32.104 --> 03:34.696
[laughs]
That... that is clever.

03:34.790 --> 03:35.714
Am I right?

03:35.941 --> 03:37.031
[laughter]

03:37.092 --> 03:39.443
That, that's good.
That's good.

03:39.461 --> 03:41.778
-Isn't it, though? [laughs]
-Yeah, yeah.

03:41.797 --> 03:44.556
[whispers] Brian, can you
explain that shirt to me later?

03:48.062 --> 03:50.229
<i> Protesters were on hand today</i>
<i> at the set of</i>

03:50.380 --> 03:52.973
<i> the new Chris Christie biopic</i>
<i> being filmed in Quahog.</i>

03:53.125 --> 03:56.126
<i>They were protesting the casting</i>
<i>of Hollywood superstar Brad Pitt</i>

03:56.219 --> 03:58.979
<i> in the lead role</i>
<i> and not a person of heft.</i>

03:59.131 --> 04:01.147
Well, Peter, I'm just glad
you're on the news

04:01.242 --> 04:04.559
for something other than sitting
on a hamster at a school event.

04:04.653 --> 04:07.320
[clamoring]

04:07.414 --> 04:09.139
Hey, they said they weren't
gonna put that!

04:09.157 --> 04:10.374
[doorbell rings]

04:11.143 --> 04:12.900
Mr. Griffin, hi.

04:12.995 --> 04:14.753
I'm Josh Universal
from the movie.

04:14.980 --> 04:17.314
I'm taking a break
from my horrific cocaine habit

04:17.332 --> 04:19.258
to ask you
to sit down with our producers

04:19.409 --> 04:22.502
for a "listening session"
to hear your concerns.

04:22.654 --> 04:25.264
And, on an unrelated note,
can I use your bathroom,

04:25.491 --> 04:27.415
and does anyone have
a rolled-up bill?

04:27.509 --> 04:29.659
Oh, of course. I got
a special five just for that.

04:30.662 --> 04:34.255
[sniffs] All right, let's get
zapped and go see a play!

04:34.349 --> 04:36.358
♪ ♪

04:38.854 --> 04:40.988
Hmm. That's odd.

04:46.269 --> 04:48.512
Mr. Griffin, thank you
for meeting with us.

04:48.530 --> 04:49.679
Have a seat.

04:49.698 --> 04:51.181
Not on my lap!

04:51.274 --> 04:52.774
Sorry. [chuckles]
I'm a little nervous.

04:52.868 --> 04:55.460
Peter Griffin,
please meet Brad Pitt.

04:55.963 --> 04:58.213
♪ ♪

04:59.358 --> 05:01.358
[gasps]
George Clooney's boyfriend?

05:01.376 --> 05:04.044
No, no. A few years ago,
he was cast in a marriage.

05:04.196 --> 05:05.953
Mr. Griffin,
we've asked you here

05:05.973 --> 05:07.622
because we understand
you have an issue

05:07.716 --> 05:09.549
with Brad playing the lead role
in our movie.

05:09.701 --> 05:13.294
We want to make sure we hear
and ignore all your concerns.

05:13.388 --> 05:15.981
Look, I know Brad Pitt is
a big star and all,

05:16.132 --> 05:17.983
but he's playing Chris Christie,
who's a fat guy.

05:18.210 --> 05:20.802
It seems unfair that
the role didn't go to a fat guy.

05:20.821 --> 05:21.987
It only makes sense.

05:22.214 --> 05:24.323
Don't you think
we should cast the best actor,

05:24.474 --> 05:25.640
letting them interpret the role,

05:25.734 --> 05:27.492
rather than depending
on physical traits?

05:27.719 --> 05:29.995
Not if you're taking the role
away from a fat guy.

05:30.146 --> 05:32.906
But, Mr. Griffin, Brad Pitt is
a highly skilled actor

05:33.000 --> 05:36.076
who's won an Oscar and lots
of garbage Golden Globes.

05:36.170 --> 05:37.502
You're not hearing my concerns.

05:37.654 --> 05:39.504
You don't know
the challenges fat guys face.

05:39.673 --> 05:41.673
What it's like
to have to rock multiple times

05:41.900 --> 05:44.234
to get off the couch,
or how it feels to have to poke

05:44.252 --> 05:46.011
a new hole in your belt
with a nail,

05:46.162 --> 05:48.088
only to realize
the end no longer

05:48.164 --> 05:49.406
tucks into the little loop,

05:49.499 --> 05:50.924
or the shame
of getting thrown out

05:51.076 --> 05:52.300
of a strip club for touching.

05:52.411 --> 05:54.411
That last thing doesn't seem
like a weight issue.

05:54.429 --> 05:56.170
You sound just like the judge!

05:56.264 --> 05:59.082
Look, the casting of this movie
is offensive to fat people,

05:59.175 --> 06:01.610
and I won't rest
until it gets shut down.

06:02.863 --> 06:04.270
Mr. Griffin, look,

06:04.423 --> 06:07.866
what if we made you our
"official fat guy consultant"?

06:08.093 --> 06:09.534
Do you think I'm an idiot?

06:09.761 --> 06:11.352
Yes! What if I told you

06:11.430 --> 06:14.188
we'll give you a P.A. who will
get you anything you want?

06:14.208 --> 06:16.099
Deal. 20 Happy Meals, please.

06:16.192 --> 06:18.268
He's actually Judd Apatow's
nephew Zack.

06:18.286 --> 06:19.769
You can't tell him what to do.

06:19.938 --> 06:21.271
In fact, you work for him.

06:21.273 --> 06:22.530
I want you to get me this thing,

06:22.624 --> 06:25.050
and I can't remember
what it is or where I saw it.

06:25.160 --> 06:28.095
Wow, I'm gonna learn so much
from his last name.

06:33.952 --> 06:36.061
[fighting and gunfire on TV]

06:37.414 --> 06:39.639
The new season of<i> White Lotus</i>
is weird.

06:39.791 --> 06:42.234
Griffins, you are looking at
the Chris Christie movie's

06:42.385 --> 06:44.403
official fat guy consultant.

06:44.554 --> 06:47.239
Boy, that's a garbage title
if I ever heard one.

06:47.390 --> 06:49.241
What? Wait a minute,
so instead of demanding

06:49.468 --> 06:51.410
they cast a plus-sized actor,
you caved

06:51.561 --> 06:53.245
when they offered you
a meaningless title?

06:53.396 --> 06:55.747
-What about
everything you fought for?
-Don't you see, Brian?

06:55.899 --> 06:58.975
Now I can work the system
from the inside with dignity.

06:58.994 --> 07:01.536
-[phone rings]
-Yes, Mr. Apatow's nephew?

07:02.572 --> 07:04.756
[deflated]
Yes, Mr. Apatow's nephew.

07:05.834 --> 07:08.318
[crying]
Yes, Mr. Apatow's nephew.

07:08.336 --> 07:10.670
What does a fat guy consultant
even do?

07:10.822 --> 07:13.323
I'm the personal
weight-gain coach for Brad Pitt.

07:13.416 --> 07:15.100
Wou-Would we get to meet him?

07:15.251 --> 07:17.177
Sure. My job is
to teach him how to think,

07:17.271 --> 07:19.104
eat and live like a fat guy.

07:19.255 --> 07:20.830
So, just like that,
you're giving up?

07:20.849 --> 07:22.107
Brian, I'm a fat guy.

07:22.258 --> 07:23.516
I got all fired up
about something,

07:23.610 --> 07:26.486
and now I'm tired
and I'd like some custard.

07:30.099 --> 07:33.100
Guys, I'd like you to meet
my new friend Brad Pitt.

07:33.195 --> 07:35.603
-Oh, my God!
-Whoa, nice to meet you.

07:35.697 --> 07:38.123
-Who's this now?
-He's a very famous actor.

07:38.200 --> 07:40.033
He's like
the white Morris Chestnut.

07:40.127 --> 07:41.943
-Oh, damn!
-Wow!

07:42.037 --> 07:44.278
I can't believe I'm sitting here
with Brad Pitt.

07:44.298 --> 07:45.613
I've got so many questions.

07:45.632 --> 07:48.115
Like, what are the other rules
of<i> Fight Club?</i>

07:48.135 --> 07:49.693
Well, the first rule is--

07:49.786 --> 07:51.211
No, I'm clear on the first rule.

07:51.305 --> 07:54.030
And I know the second rule is
just repeating the first.

07:54.049 --> 07:55.381
But there's got to be
loads more.

07:55.476 --> 07:58.793
Like, I got to think
"no sack attacks" is on there.

07:58.870 --> 08:00.053
Hey, Brad.
Any chance I could get

08:00.147 --> 08:01.888
Jennifer Aniston's number
from you?

08:01.982 --> 08:03.148
I know she's got to be
a nightmare,

08:03.375 --> 08:05.709
but she keeps it
so freakin' tight.

08:05.727 --> 08:06.726
Okay, enough small talk.

08:06.820 --> 08:08.228
Let's do
what I brought him here for:

08:08.380 --> 08:10.063
to break the Internet
with a group

08:10.157 --> 08:12.824
-head-smushed-together selfie.
-[phone beeps]

08:12.993 --> 08:14.308
[camera clicks]

08:14.328 --> 08:16.995
Kevin Spacey?
Get out of here.

08:17.222 --> 08:19.222
You're not allowed to be
in head-smushed-together photos

08:19.241 --> 08:20.332
after what you did.

08:20.483 --> 08:23.059
Not guilty
on all British counts.

08:23.078 --> 08:25.545
[chuckles] Oh, that rascal.

08:28.583 --> 08:30.416
[knocking]

08:30.511 --> 08:33.570
Hi, you must be Peter's wife.
I'm Brad.

08:33.663 --> 08:35.597
♪ ♪

08:37.075 --> 08:40.076
Oh, I know who you are.
I'm-- [screams]

08:40.169 --> 08:42.003
Hi, I'm-- [screams]

08:42.022 --> 08:43.429
Stewart. Charmed.

08:43.582 --> 08:45.248
I know you dump people
when they're 40,

08:45.267 --> 08:48.026
but that still gives us
39 good years.

08:48.253 --> 08:50.177
Pleased to meet you, Mr. Pitt.

08:50.272 --> 08:52.346
Um, when you did
that movie<i> Snatch,</i>

08:52.407 --> 08:54.515
did you know
that also means something else?

08:54.609 --> 08:56.183
Because it very much does.

08:56.278 --> 08:58.762
That's a sticky handshake
you got there, Chris.

08:58.780 --> 09:00.764
Peter, I was wondering
if I could spend some time

09:00.782 --> 09:03.283
with you and your family,
observing how you live

09:03.435 --> 09:05.710
and how you eat,
to prepare for the role.

09:05.862 --> 09:07.120
Sure, I'd be glad to help.

09:07.214 --> 09:09.606
Wow, I ain't had a celebrity
ask me for a favor

09:09.657 --> 09:12.125
since Jeremy Renner asked me
to shovel out his driveway.

09:12.219 --> 09:16.037
-[engine idling]
-Uh, Jeremy, in light of
recent events, uh...

09:16.056 --> 09:18.557
could ol' Pete borrow your skis?

09:21.395 --> 09:24.137
Okay, Brad, I'm gonna teach you
to be a fat guy.

09:24.231 --> 09:26.306
For starters,
this is where we eat.

09:26.458 --> 09:29.401
Um, excuse me, Mr. Pitt,
but would you mind

09:29.628 --> 09:31.311
if I FaceTime my friends
with you here?

09:31.463 --> 09:33.721
Oh, my God, they'll go crazy!

09:33.815 --> 09:35.240
Sure, Meg, it'd be my pleasure.

09:35.391 --> 09:38.159
-[squeals]
-[FaceTime app ringing]

09:47.421 --> 09:49.087
Oh, boy.

09:50.239 --> 09:52.465
Oh, this-this is sad.

09:53.985 --> 09:57.429
Oh, this-this is just... Oh...

09:57.656 --> 10:00.006
Why don't I just take this,
dear.

10:00.100 --> 10:01.725
-[ringing stops]
-[phone beeps]

10:06.255 --> 10:08.422
Okay, Brad, now,
another fat guy rule is that

10:08.516 --> 10:10.591
when you're out at restaurants,
always act like

10:10.611 --> 10:12.110
you're on the fence
about dessert.

10:12.261 --> 10:14.337
So, folks, we thinking dessert?

10:14.339 --> 10:16.114
Seriously? You must be joking.

10:16.341 --> 10:19.117
I cannot move.
No, sir. No way.

10:19.268 --> 10:20.860
Absolutely stuffed to the gills.

10:21.012 --> 10:22.269
Gonna have to take a rain check.

10:22.364 --> 10:24.514
Although... No, no,
I can't even suggest it.

10:24.607 --> 10:28.017
We are done. Done-a-roo.
Check, please.

10:28.036 --> 10:29.443
Although... just thinking,

10:29.463 --> 10:31.112
I don't know when
we'll be back here.

10:31.206 --> 10:32.964
I read about
the award-winning pastry chef--

10:33.116 --> 10:34.782
Wait, what am I saying? No! No.

10:34.909 --> 10:36.134
Stop me, please,
someone, please.

10:36.303 --> 10:37.861
Bring the check now.

10:37.954 --> 10:40.121
Okay, you know what, we'll get
one order and we'll all share.

10:40.215 --> 10:42.140
One dessert, one dish,
five spoons.

10:42.367 --> 10:43.700
Whoever wants can have some.

10:43.718 --> 10:45.644
One plate. One of everything.
My plate.

10:45.795 --> 10:47.729
One spoon. No share.

10:50.466 --> 10:52.317
Now, Brad, if you're gonna
play a fat guy on camera,

10:52.468 --> 10:55.195
you got to learn
how to do the rope swing.

10:57.473 --> 10:59.199
Okay, let me show you
how it's done.

10:59.993 --> 11:01.534
[groans]

11:04.572 --> 11:06.814
900,000 views.

11:06.833 --> 11:09.058
-I'm learning so much.
-That's great.

11:09.152 --> 11:11.060
Hey, can you click
on a porn site for me?

11:11.079 --> 11:12.578
Otherwise I got to
peck it with my nose

11:12.731 --> 11:14.631
like a tic-tac-toe chicken.

11:21.164 --> 11:22.922
Here you go.

11:23.074 --> 11:24.516
Thanks so much, Mrs. Griffin.

11:24.743 --> 11:26.092
I love a home-cooked meal.

11:26.244 --> 11:28.836
Well, we are
so happy to have you.

11:28.855 --> 11:30.263
-How's Shiloh?
-Who?

11:30.415 --> 11:31.839
-How's Maddox?
-Who?

11:31.858 --> 11:33.507
-How's Zahara?
-Who?

11:33.527 --> 11:34.859
-How's Pax?
-Who?

11:35.011 --> 11:36.236
-How's Vivienne?
-Who?

11:36.271 --> 11:37.511
-How's Knox?
-Who?

11:37.531 --> 11:39.364
Ignore her,
she can be so annoying.

11:39.515 --> 11:41.274
Sometimes I wish
I had a private plane

11:41.368 --> 11:43.410
just so I could choke her on it.

11:47.098 --> 11:48.431
Hey, can I get you anything?

11:48.524 --> 11:51.617
Another pork-n-Cheetos sandwich
or a buffalo latte?

11:51.770 --> 11:53.027
I'm good, Peter, thanks.

11:53.046 --> 11:54.454
[director]
Brad, you're up!

11:54.622 --> 11:55.714
[groans]

11:55.865 --> 11:58.124
[grunting]

11:58.218 --> 12:00.293
-Ah!
-[director] Brad? Are you okay?

12:00.445 --> 12:03.037
My back. I threw out my back.
I can't move.

12:03.056 --> 12:04.781
Hey, since you can't
really move right now,

12:04.799 --> 12:06.540
this is probably
a good time to ask,

12:06.560 --> 12:08.393
what's Juliette Lewis
really like?

12:08.620 --> 12:11.545
[straining]
Nice. Talented. Professional.

12:11.565 --> 12:14.357
-A little shrill.
-Yeah, a little shrill.
Yeah, that sounds right.

12:15.293 --> 12:17.961
[groaning, panting]

12:17.979 --> 12:20.221
I don't think I can walk.

12:20.298 --> 12:22.315
We can't push back our schedule
any more.

12:22.391 --> 12:24.075
If Brad's injured,
what are we gonna do?

12:24.152 --> 12:25.802
We'll need a new Chris Christie.

12:25.820 --> 12:29.205
But who could possibly play
that role on such short notice?

12:30.733 --> 12:31.991
I can play that role.

12:32.143 --> 12:34.235
Griffin,
you're not even an actor.

12:34.254 --> 12:36.829
No, but what I am is
a real fat guy.

12:36.982 --> 12:38.572
Brad Pitt was never
the right choice.

12:38.592 --> 12:41.575
This role calls for
real-life fat guy authenticity.

12:41.653 --> 12:43.486
I mean, would<i> Transparent</i>
have been as good

12:43.505 --> 12:45.171
if they just put a guy
in a dress?

12:45.265 --> 12:47.081
Would Neil Patrick Harris
have been as funny

12:47.175 --> 12:48.749
on<i> How I Met Your Mother</i>
if he wasn't

12:48.843 --> 12:50.751
a known heterosexual horndog?

12:50.845 --> 12:52.512
Would<i> Tropic Thunder</i>
have been as authentic

12:52.606 --> 12:56.065
if Robert Downey Jr. wasn't
a dignified Black man?

12:57.168 --> 12:58.926
We're in a jam.
What do you think?

12:59.095 --> 13:00.761
I don't think
we have any other choice.

13:00.930 --> 13:03.172
All right, Griffin,
you got the part.

13:03.266 --> 13:05.024
Awesome! I'm gonna
FaceTime my friends.

13:05.101 --> 13:06.859
They're gonna be
so excited for me.

13:07.012 --> 13:09.162
[FaceTime app ringing]

13:12.959 --> 13:14.626
Oh, boy.

13:15.870 --> 13:17.629
Oh, this-this is sad.

13:23.528 --> 13:25.637
[TV announcer]
<i> We now return to</i>
<i> a steamy business drama</i>

13:25.788 --> 13:27.880
<i> where no one understands</i>
<i> what's happening.</i>

13:28.033 --> 13:30.624
<i> Are you saying we should forge</i>
<i> the EBITDA projections</i>

13:30.644 --> 13:32.218
<i> -for the quarterlies?</i>
<i> -No.</i>

13:32.312 --> 13:33.645
<i> I'm saying</i>
<i> we declare a revenue-miss</i>

13:33.796 --> 13:35.296
<i>while issuing additional shares</i>

13:35.315 --> 13:37.723
<i> based on reduced</i>
<i> capitalization estimates.</i>

13:37.892 --> 13:39.967
<i> Jim, you're in grave danger</i>

13:39.986 --> 13:41.561
<i> of violating</i>
<i> the Glass-Steagall Act.</i>

13:41.713 --> 13:44.213
[Chris]
They haven't shown a bare ass
in three weeks!

13:44.307 --> 13:45.898
<i> Show me your ass, Jim.</i>

13:46.051 --> 13:47.141
[Chris]
And I'm back.

13:47.160 --> 13:50.053
Griffins,
you are looking at the new lead

13:50.146 --> 13:51.904
in the Chris Christie movie.

13:51.981 --> 13:54.499
You? Wh-What happened
to Brad Pitt?

13:54.650 --> 13:56.726
It's what I've been saying
all along, Lois.

13:56.819 --> 13:58.061
He can't do what I do.

13:58.079 --> 14:00.112
He doesn't bring
the fat guy authenticity.

14:00.173 --> 14:02.231
His sweat doesn't smell
like french fries.

14:02.325 --> 14:04.250
He doesn't bring
the sky-high blood pressure

14:04.344 --> 14:05.902
or the jolting sleep apnea.

14:05.995 --> 14:07.846
I have that gift.
That's why.

14:07.997 --> 14:09.906
Peter, this is ridiculous.

14:10.075 --> 14:11.516
You can't play Chris Christie.

14:11.667 --> 14:13.500
You're not even an actor.

14:13.578 --> 14:14.744
Oh, no?

14:14.762 --> 14:18.581
Yes, Lois! Yes! Yes! Oh!

14:18.600 --> 14:20.007
Sound familiar?

14:20.026 --> 14:22.085
-But how do you...?
-Squirt gun full of Ivory.

14:22.178 --> 14:25.530
Sorry, Lunchables, I'm afraid
I've lost my appetite.

14:25.699 --> 14:27.090
Peter, I'm proud of you.

14:27.092 --> 14:28.441
You're actually making
important strides

14:28.535 --> 14:31.018
on behalf of inclusivity
and cultural sensitivity.

14:31.037 --> 14:32.203
Yeah, I'm all for that stuff.

14:32.372 --> 14:33.854
As long as we don't
got to take down

14:33.874 --> 14:35.281
the Confederate statue
in the yard.

14:35.375 --> 14:37.266
That's for history and learning.

14:37.285 --> 14:38.710
Even if they did
come in second place

14:38.861 --> 14:40.286
out of two armies in a war.

14:40.380 --> 14:43.439
-So, how'd we do?
-Second place, baby.

14:43.532 --> 14:44.941
Hey, not bad.

14:45.034 --> 14:47.468
Silver medal. Whoo!

14:51.057 --> 14:53.332
Okay, Peter,
so, in this next scene,

14:53.393 --> 14:56.377
Christie would probably struggle
in the heat and sun

14:56.396 --> 14:58.379
on the George Washington Bridge.

14:58.398 --> 15:00.881
You presume to lecture me
what it's like?

15:00.901 --> 15:03.142
How dare you thinsplain to me?

15:03.294 --> 15:05.904
Talk to me
when your BMI is over 35.

15:06.055 --> 15:07.888
Wow, a real live movie set.

15:07.908 --> 15:10.057
So cool to be here
for the magic.

15:10.076 --> 15:11.801
Yeah, and look,
there's a child star

15:11.819 --> 15:13.077
who's getting an hour of school.

15:13.304 --> 15:15.896
Okay, Billy, now,
what color is this?

15:15.974 --> 15:17.564
-Blue?
-Close enough.

15:17.584 --> 15:18.824
Now get back out there

15:18.977 --> 15:21.644
and be the most distracting
part of any film.

15:21.663 --> 15:22.754
♪ ♪

15:22.905 --> 15:24.756
♪<i> Making a movie</i> ♪

15:24.907 --> 15:28.151
♪<i> Not as glamorous as it seems</i> ♪

15:28.169 --> 15:29.652
♪<i> Standing around</i> ♪

15:29.671 --> 15:32.155
♪<i> For three hours</i>
<i> just to move a light</i> ♪

15:32.173 --> 15:35.708
♪<i> Tripping over thick cables</i>
<i> everywhere</i> ♪

15:35.860 --> 15:41.180
♪<i> Spending all day shooting</i>
<i> one ten-second scene, yeah</i> ♪

15:41.332 --> 15:45.193
♪<i> Waving flies</i>
<i> off the craft service table</i> ♪

15:47.005 --> 15:48.337
♪<i> Making a movie</i> ♪

15:48.431 --> 15:51.674
♪<i> Way more tedious</i>
<i> than it seems</i> ♪

15:51.767 --> 15:55.453
♪<i> The most important job</i>
<i> is the editor</i> ♪

15:55.680 --> 15:59.457
♪<i> Staring at a frame</i>
<i> for 18 hours straight</i> ♪

15:59.684 --> 16:02.702
♪<i> Most of them snap</i>
<i> and go crazy</i> ♪

16:02.796 --> 16:07.799
♪<i> Even a dumb cartoon like this</i>
<i> takes 18 months</i> ♪

16:07.950 --> 16:12.428
♪<i> What are we all doing?</i> ♪

16:16.309 --> 16:18.142
[camera shutters clicking]

16:18.294 --> 16:20.720
Oh, Peter,
your big movie premiere.

16:20.888 --> 16:22.538
This is so exciting!

16:22.631 --> 16:25.391
Did Dr. Hartman bring a woman
in a coma as his date?

16:25.560 --> 16:28.635
Hey, guys, big night, huh?
See you in there.

16:28.655 --> 16:30.563
-[crowd clamoring]
-[camera shutters clicking]

16:30.715 --> 16:33.974
Oh, God, here come those
mindless entertainment reporters

16:33.994 --> 16:35.901
who only want to know,
"Who are you wearing?"

16:35.996 --> 16:37.720
-Stewie!
-Stewie.
-Over here, Stewie.

16:37.739 --> 16:40.223
How do you respond to those
who accuse your show

16:40.241 --> 16:42.241
of trafficking in
decades of misogyny,

16:42.393 --> 16:45.061
homophobia and racially
insensitive stereotyping?

16:45.230 --> 16:47.654
Uh... Thom Browne, thank you.

16:47.674 --> 16:49.007
Go, Brian. Go, go, go, go, go.

16:49.234 --> 16:51.751
And here's the star of the film,
Peter Griffin.

16:51.845 --> 16:53.344
What are you wearing tonight,
Peter?

16:53.421 --> 16:56.163
Well, Tom, the shirt is actually
two shirts sewn together.

16:56.182 --> 16:58.516
The jacket is stolen
from a steak house maître d',

16:58.667 --> 17:00.243
and the pants are a towel.

17:00.245 --> 17:02.762
You know, I hear you were
quite the prankster on set.

17:02.914 --> 17:03.929
Well, it wasn't so much pranks

17:04.024 --> 17:05.264
as yelling
and shouting at women.

17:05.416 --> 17:06.766
Yeah, a lot of 'em aren't here
tonight.

17:06.918 --> 17:09.268
They're doing some town hall
meeting with Gloria Allred.

17:09.420 --> 17:11.154
Ah, we'll see what happens.

17:16.352 --> 17:17.593
The after-party's at a Panera

17:17.612 --> 17:20.204
that's still open
to normal customers.

17:20.431 --> 17:22.540
[cheering]

17:22.691 --> 17:24.024
Thank you all for coming.

17:24.193 --> 17:26.269
-[Quagmire] Giggity.
-It was a lot of hard work.

17:26.287 --> 17:29.213
-[Quagmire] Giggity.
-And thanks to the unnecessarily
long writers' strike,

17:29.365 --> 17:32.366
we were unable to write
a third joke for this speech.

17:32.460 --> 17:34.034
[cheering]

17:34.054 --> 17:35.945
-Hey!
-Ow!

17:35.963 --> 17:37.238
That's your father's movie
up there.

17:37.240 --> 17:38.948
Pay attention, you dope.

17:38.966 --> 17:41.184
♪ ♪

17:42.804 --> 17:45.271
[clamoring on screen]

17:46.399 --> 17:47.456
Repeat after me.

17:47.625 --> 17:50.293
-I's am governor.
-I's am governor.

17:50.311 --> 17:52.962
-Youse are not.
-Youse are not.

17:52.964 --> 17:55.648
Big Pussy didn't deserve
to die like that

17:55.800 --> 17:56.908
in<i> The Sopranos.</i>

17:57.059 --> 17:58.484
But he was a freakin' rat!

17:58.578 --> 18:00.986
Congratulations, you are
the governor of New Jersey.

18:01.139 --> 18:03.230
Now let's all root
for the Jets and the Mets

18:03.324 --> 18:04.990
like the idiots we are.

18:05.085 --> 18:07.234
[cheering]

18:07.328 --> 18:09.337
♪ ♪

18:10.498 --> 18:12.965
[thunder crashing]

18:14.335 --> 18:17.320
Lord, please protect us
from this coming hurricane.

18:17.413 --> 18:20.172
It's bad enough you gave me
the same first and last name.

18:20.266 --> 18:22.825
Please don't let me be killed
by a Sandy.

18:22.844 --> 18:26.662
The fellas at the Y would never
let me hear the end of it. Amen.

18:26.831 --> 18:28.831
♪ ♪

18:28.850 --> 18:30.775
[crying]

18:30.926 --> 18:33.336
Oh, Chris, you're dying.

18:33.429 --> 18:35.838
Don't remember me like this.

18:35.931 --> 18:37.949
Remember me stuffed
like a sausage

18:38.100 --> 18:40.785
into that NYPD softball uniform.

18:40.936 --> 18:43.937
♪<i> But I would walk 500 miles</i> ♪

18:43.957 --> 18:47.416
-[scattered clapping]
-♪<i> And I would walk 500.</i> ♪

18:48.628 --> 18:50.444
[feigning enthusiasm]
Hey, that was terrific.

18:50.463 --> 18:52.964
[forced]
Oh, what an achievement.

18:53.115 --> 18:54.540
[chuckles awkwardly]
You really did it, buddy.

18:54.692 --> 18:56.525
What are you guys
talking about? I stunk.

18:56.619 --> 18:57.618
I can't act at all.

18:57.712 --> 18:59.011
No...

18:59.121 --> 19:02.198
You were, uh,
very believably fat.

19:02.216 --> 19:03.957
Didn't you notice half the time

19:03.977 --> 19:05.309
I was staring
right into the camera?

19:05.461 --> 19:08.053
They had to use peanut butter
to get me on my mark.

19:08.206 --> 19:09.221
Yeah, but you've done
a great thing

19:09.374 --> 19:11.223
for authenticity
and inclusivity.

19:11.376 --> 19:12.558
I don't even know
what those words mean,

19:12.652 --> 19:14.894
I just like to see your tail wag
when you say 'em.

19:14.988 --> 19:17.488
Peter, you're giving
the marginalized a voice.

19:17.715 --> 19:18.898
How are they marginalized?

19:18.992 --> 19:21.141
The whole country's full
of dumb, fat [bleep].

19:21.310 --> 19:24.570
Now more than ever, we need
authenticity and inclusivity.

19:24.722 --> 19:26.831
No, Brian.
What we need is good actors.

19:27.058 --> 19:28.724
I don't care if they're Black,
white, tall,

19:28.743 --> 19:30.001
short, thin, fat.

19:30.152 --> 19:31.502
Gay, straight--
you forgot those ones.

19:31.729 --> 19:33.838
Look, I-I admit
I thought acting was easy.

19:34.065 --> 19:36.007
And maybe I was blinded
by all the praise I got

19:36.234 --> 19:37.733
from Harvey Weinstein.

19:37.752 --> 19:40.736
Peter, Harvey Weinstein hasn't
had clout for like six years.

19:40.905 --> 19:43.088
Oh, boy. Then I may have done
some things I'll regret.

19:43.908 --> 19:46.242
I don't know, I guess,
as a fat guy, I-I got offended

19:46.260 --> 19:48.427
that Chris Christie wasn't
played by a fat guy.

19:48.521 --> 19:50.855
But turns out it just needed
to be a good actor.

19:51.006 --> 19:53.006
Maybe we should all
spend less time judging

19:53.026 --> 19:54.266
and more time enjoying

19:54.360 --> 19:56.252
what different actors
bring to different roles.

19:56.387 --> 19:58.679
That's the magic
of movies and TV.

19:58.773 --> 20:00.105
[Chris]
And stepson porn.

20:00.274 --> 20:02.591
Chris, you don't have
to join every conversation.

20:02.685 --> 20:05.018
[murmuring]

20:05.112 --> 20:06.278
Okay, look, look, I understand

20:06.431 --> 20:08.355
not everyone will agree
on this issue,

20:08.374 --> 20:10.374
but let's discuss it
in a civilized manner

20:10.526 --> 20:12.968
by making death threats
from our individual homes

20:13.028 --> 20:14.712
to one another on the Internet.

20:14.863 --> 20:16.589
[phone chimes]

20:19.277 --> 20:20.551
Right back at you, buddy.

20:26.451 --> 20:29.227
Well, I'm sorry your movie
didn't go over well, Peter.

20:29.454 --> 20:30.953
Yeah, the money was good,
but I got tired of

20:30.972 --> 20:32.063
all the one-night stands.

20:32.214 --> 20:33.064
-What?
-Huh?

20:33.215 --> 20:34.640
Sorry, my ears have been clogged

20:34.792 --> 20:36.717
since I made out with that guy
from the film crew.

20:36.736 --> 20:37.884
-What?
-Huh?

20:37.904 --> 20:39.144
Well, I got to say, Bri,

20:39.297 --> 20:40.238
it might not have worked out
for Dad,

20:40.389 --> 20:42.723
but I sure got bit
by the acting bug.

20:42.742 --> 20:43.983
Really? You want to be an actor?

20:44.151 --> 20:46.635
Oh, yeah. I'd be great
in<i> Streetcar.</i>

20:46.654 --> 20:50.248
Stella! Stella!

20:50.399 --> 20:51.732
What?!

20:51.751 --> 20:54.043
Is Aidan home?
